  "description": "MBOX-482 (P2) — Microsoft 365 / Graph egress, token-as-data sibling of MailBOX-Send / MailBOX-Imap-Send. The dashboard's send trigger (lib/n8n.ts) routes here via N8N_GRAPH_WEBHOOK_URL when the draft's account is provider='microsoft'. Same { draft_id } contract + send_attempt_at CAS idempotency lock (migration 025) as the Gmail/IMAP paths; writes the provider-neutral drafts.provider_message_id. Auth is token-as-data: Get Graph Token mints an app-only bearer per send from the dashboard minter (app/api/internal/graph/access-token) — NO n8n credential. Graph sendMail composes a reply (Re: subject, body, To: original sender) via POST /users/{account_email}/sendMail (app-only token acts for that mailbox). EXPRESSION CONVENTION (MBOX-344): Graph sendMail + Mark Sent Graph read $('Load Draft Graph').item.json.* — never bare $json — because Acquire Send Lock (RETURNING id) sits between. S-MP RESIDUAL: flat reply (To/Subject/body); true RFC In-Reply-To/References threading headers are a follow-up (kill-criterion: ship flat + flag degraded, same as IMAP). ON IMPORT: re-point the Postgres credential id if it differs; set HERMES_INTERNAL_TOKEN on n8n.",
